<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-27T06:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-27T06:25:00-05:00" n="760" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.00/310: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-27T14:00:00+02:35">August 27, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received August 27—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>83. In view of fantastic rumors which I understand some of the
                                    numerous foreign correspondents are broadcasting for lack of
                                    something better to do I desire to assure the Department that
                                    the city is perfectly calm, that no immediate evacuation has
                                    been ordered either of natives or foreigners and that any
                                    foreigner departing can obtain sufficient foreign exchange to
                                    take him home. Many merchants are changing paper money into
                                    silver which caused mild run on the bank.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>